  "texts": [
    "We observe that the surrogate (second column) accurately captures both the phase lag and amplitude of these oscillations, while the diffusion-only ablation (third column) collapses to near-monotonic trends.",
    "The GNN-only ablation (fourth column), besides following a completely deterministic dynamic, completely diverges from the ground truth.",
    "The number of preys under Ψ 1, for instance, quickly reaches a plateau at a value of 750 (not shown), almost twice the real one.",
    "We perform the same analysis for alternative parameterizations Ψ 2, Ψ 3 (included in Supplementary Section C) that show different types of dynamics, as the population of predators and/or preys may exhibit monotonic extinctions.",
    "In all cases, the surrogate faithfully reproduces monotonic declines or single-peak dynamics and both ablations fail."
